It has been confirmed a man and a woman, both 34, and four young girls aged nine, six, four and two were killed when their 4WD collided with a road train on the Stuart Highway in late September. Police confirmed the family were from Lajamanu, a remote community of 600 people west of Katherine. Police said the family were travelling in their newly purchased 2009 Mitsubishu Pajero when it veered into the path of a three-trailer road train on the highway, south of Pine Creek. The road train rolled to the side of the road, spilling thousands of litres of fuel which soon erupted into a "fireball" explosion.
